result.execSummary:
The defendant Susan E. Bauer was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess/Illegally Obtained Prescription, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 450.11(7)(h).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant appears with counsel Damon Stichert.  Gerald Fox appears for the State.  DA Fox calls first witness, D.S., sworn, testifies.  Patrol duty on March 7, 2016 and summoned to the courthouse to meet with LE personnel.  During a search prior to a court hearing for the defendant, 2 green pill bottles were found in defendant's purse with the names scratched off.  Witness ID's the defendant.  Record reflects ID.  She states what the drugs were and that they were ID'd by using drugs.com.  They were Ritalin and Diazepam.  Need a valid prescription for those drugs.  When defendant exited the courtroom defendant was placed under arrest.  Defense cross-examines the witness.  The pharmacy on the bottles did not have any prescriptions on file for the defendant.  Re-direct by the State.  State moves for bind over.   Defense has no witnesse or comments.  Court finds probable cause is found.  Bound over for trial.  State files the Information.  Defense waives the reading and enters NGP's to both counts and 16TR932.  Court sets for pre-trial 6-29 at 10:00 and status for 7-11 at 3:00.  Bond will continue.
